adjectives.description: profuse (comparative more profuse, superlative most profuse)

entries.meaning: abundant or generous to the point of excess.
examples: She grew profuse amounts of zucchini and pumpkins.
profuse hospitality; profuse apologies; profuse expenditure

verbs.description: profuse (third-person singular simple present profuses, present participle profusing, simple past and past participle profused)

entries.meaning: (obsolete) To pour out; to give or spend liberally; to lavish; to squander.
